# Keylogger Lab – Controlled Virtual Environment

## Overview

This repository documents a cybersecurity lab conducted in an isolated virtual environment to understand how keystroke logging techniques work and why endpoint security solutions are important.

## Lab Environment

* Attacker Machine: Kali Linux Virtual Machine
* Target Machine: Windows 10 Virtual Machine
* Network: Isolated and controlled for educational testing

## Objective

The goal of this lab was to study the behavior of a proof-of-concept keylogger and observe how captured keyboard input could be transmitted from one system to another in a controlled setting.

## Outcome

After execution on the Windows 10 VM, keystrokes entered on the target system were successfully displayed on the Kali Linux machine, demonstrating the communication flow between the two virtual machines.

## Skills Practiced

* Virtual machine configuration
* Network connectivity between VMs
* Process execution and monitoring
* Understanding keystroke logging concepts
* Basic client-server communication
* Security awareness and defensive implications

## Disclaimer

This project was performed entirely within an isolated laboratory environment for educational and research purposes. No unauthorized systems or users were involved, and the exercise was conducted solely to improve understanding of cybersecurity concepts and defensive practices.
